---
const items = [
  { num: "01", title: "Last-Mile Book Rescue", sub: "For 80% manuscripts that aren't landing.",
    body: "You don't need a full ghostwriter. You have a manuscript that's eighty percent there—drafted by you, a coauthor, or an AI that reads exactly like AI. We diagnose what's wrong (missing argument, broken character logic, no felt stakes) and rebuild what isn't earning the page. Structural repair. Voice reconstruction. Story insertion." },
  { num: "02", title: "Page to Screen", sub: "For books with a film or series future.",
    body: "Platte is a credited screenwriter on Lionsgate's The Best Christmas Pageant Ever (2024 · 92% Critics / 97% Audiences), with active film representation through Plain Text Talent. Authors whose books have a film or series future engage us at the architecture stage—so the manuscript is built with adaptation in mind, and positioned for the right Hollywood ear when ready." },
  { num: "03", title: "Curriculum & Productization", sub: "Tools that transform organizations.",
    body: "Three decades of curriculum design for FranklinCovey, VitalSmarts (Crucial Conversations), and ZengerFolkman—programs delivered to millions across six continents. When your book leads to a workshop, a cohort program, an assessment, or an online course, the architect of the book is the architect of the curriculum. No handoff." },
];
---

<section class="section fade-in">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block; margin-bottom:1rem;">What We Build</span>
      <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Three things most ghostwriting firms <span class="display-italic">can't do.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede" style="font-size:clamp(1.05rem,1.7vw,1.3rem);">
        Books are platforms, not endpoints. The pieces below are the work most ghostwriting firms
        can't do.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card-invert struct">
      <p class="eyebrow" style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.9rem;">The Structural Difference</p>
      <h3 class="h3" style="color:#f4f1ea; font-style:italic; margin-bottom:1rem;">Specialist, not generalist. Embedded, not networked.</h3>
      <p class="on-dark-soft" style="line-height:1.62; margin:0;">
        Most firms operate on a generalist-plus-network model. A salesperson signs you. A project
        manager checks in. A contracted writer you'll never speak to drafts your book.
        <strong style="color:#fff; font-weight:600;">The people you meet at the beginning are the
        people who write the book.</strong> We are a boutique with a handful of clients, nearly
        all referrals.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="builds">
      {items.map((it) => (
        <div class="build-row">
          <span class="build-num display">{it.num}</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="h3" style="margin-bottom:0.2rem;">{it.title}</h3>
            <p class="build-sub display-italic">{it.sub}</p>
            <p class="body-text" style="margin:0;">{it.body}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .struct { padding: 2.2rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .builds { margin: 0; }
  .build-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 4.5rem 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 2rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule); }
  .build-row:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule); }
  .build-num { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1; color: var(--color-blue); opacity: 0.85; }
  .build-sub { color: var(--color-blue); font-size: 1.05rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .build-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.6rem; }
    .build-num { font-size: 1.8rem; }
  }
</style>
